# Prettier formatting

This repo uses Prettier (`.prettierrc.json`). Do not rely on approximate style — run the formatter.

## After editing files

When you create or modify source files, run Prettier on **only those paths** before finishing:

```bash
pnpm exec prettier --write path/to/file1.tsx path/to/file2.ts
```

Do **not** run `pnpm run format` / `prettier --write .` unless the user explicitly asks for a full-repo format.

## Config to match (do not fight these)

- `printWidth`: 80
- `tabWidth`: 2, `useTabs`: false
- `semi`: true
- `singleQuote`: false
- `trailingComma`: "es5"
- `arrowParens`: "always"

## Skip

- Files ignored by `.prettierignore` (currently `*.json`, `*.yaml`, `*.yml`)
- Generated / binary assets under `public/` data dumps unless the user asked to edit them

## Do not put Prettier in `dev` or `build`

Keep formatting out of those scripts. Use this post-edit step (and optional format-on-save / pre-commit) instead.
